N o t e: A second species 
<emphasis box="[466,582,256,278]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1667">H. hirsutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CHAMPION G" box="[592,779,256,278]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1667" pagination="65 - 117" refId="ref10223" refString="CHAMPION G. C. (1898): Family Aradidae. - In: Biologia Centrali Americana. Insecta. Rhynchota 2: 65 - 117, plates 5 - 7." type="journal article" year="1898">CHAMPION (1898)</bibRefCitation>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1085,257,278]" name="Panama" pageId="8" pageNumber="1667">Panama</collectingCountry>
mainly based on different colouration. Neither CHAMPION (loc. cit.) nor USINGER &amp; MATSUDA (1959: 370) studied both 
<typeStatus box="[547,601,315,336]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1667">types</typeStatus>
and the question if the latter is a valid taxon is still not decided. KORMILEV &amp; FROESCHNER (1987) listed both taxa.
</paragraph>
